        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 2 at 6:59PM CDT by NWS Birmingham AL</headline>
        <description>At 659 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Heiberger, or 9 miles south of Brent, moving
northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Lawley, Trio, Centreville, Judson College, Radford, Vaiden, West
Centreville, Folsom, Brent, Bibb County Airport, Talladega National
Forest, Heiberger, Oakmulgee, Eoline, Sprott, Marion, Ellards,
Randolph, West Blocton, and Jemison.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 900 PM CDT for
central and south central Alabama.</instruction>
